meta {
  name: Clone Site Admin Template
  type: http
  seq: 11
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/lab-panels/{{siteAdminLabPanelId}}/clone
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{businessAccessToken}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "masterDataId": "{{masterDataId}}"
  }
}

script:post-response {
  const data = res.getBody() && res.getBody().data;
  if (data && data.id) bru.setEnvVar("clonedLabPanelId", data.id);
}

docs {
  Clone a SITE_ADMIN lab-panel template (the `:id` in the URL) into the caller's
  tenant catalogue. Business JWT. **Only `masterDataId` is sent in the body** —
  `tenantId`/`branchId` come from the JWT and the target master data (CLAUDE.md
  §4.7). Captures `clonedLabPanelId`.

  Behaviour: creates the panel as `source = "TENANT"` with fresh ids, then for
  each included test it **clones the referenced SITE_ADMIN template test into the
  tenant** (deduplicated within the request) and rewires the join rows to point at
  the new tenant tests — so the cloned panel references tenant-owned tests, not the
  templates. The whole operation (panel + cloned tests + join rows) is one
  transaction; any failure rolls back with no partial rows.

  - `siteAdminLabPanelId` is a live SITE_ADMIN template → else 404
    `LAB_PANEL_NOT_FOUND`; a referenced template test missing → 404
    `LAB_TEST_NOT_FOUND`.
  - `masterDataId` must belong to the caller's tenant → else 404
    `MASTER_DATA_NOT_FOUND`.
  - 409 `LAB_PANEL_NAME_CONFLICT` / `LAB_PANEL_CODE_CONFLICT` (or a lab-test code
    clash) if a name/code already exists (active) in the target master data.
}
